<br>
Mrylokar's Bracer drops I belive in Sebilis, and has unlimited charges of summon throwing dagger, which summons a stack of throwing daggers (shockingly enough).  Not amazing range there either.<br>
<br>
Honestly, throwing is pointless till you're 60, and only situationaly then... there is NO situation where a throwing weapon is better than an arrow until that point, since arrows do so much more damage and are so much cheaper per shot, plus with such higher range.  It doesn't matter that you can deadly strike for 24 damage with your 6 damage throwing knife if I'm shooting 45 damage arrows that hit for a max of over 90, no crits needed.  Plus Throwing weapons have very low range... 65 for the summoned daggers, less for other weapons.  The only summonable throwers worth using are from the dusty worker's pouch from Ssra, but that's likely rather out of reach... and they still only have a 170 range.  For comparison, the top level fletched bow, non cultural, has 200 range, and it's very cheap and easy to make stacks of 150 range arrows, for a total range of 350.<br>
<br>
